Wash and dry produce. Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips.

Heat a large, dry, preferably #nonstick pan{} over high heat. Add bell pepper, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and a small splash of water to hot pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until bell pepper is softened and water has absorbed, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} and @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} to pan with bell pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage is almost cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara sauce{5%oz cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sausage is coated and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer sausage mixture to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle one half of each tortilla with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}. Top with sausage mixture, then sprinkle with @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat @butter{1%tbsp} in pan used for sausage over medium-high heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer quesadillas to a #cutting board{}; slice into thirds and divide between plates. Serve.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter and cook quesadillas in batches.

> Tip: Lower heat if quesadillas begin to brown too quickly.